@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor transparent
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced
skinparam titleFontSize 18
skinparam rectangleFontSize 13
skinparam legendFontSize 12

title xer::image coordinate and stride model

rectangle "Logical canvas\ncoordinates are (x, y)\norigin = top-left" as logical
rectangle "Owning canvas<Width, Height, Policy>\nvisible width = Width\nheight = Height\nstorage stride = Width" as owning
rectangle "Future stride-aware view\nvisible width = width\nheight = height\nstorage stride may be larger" as view

logical --> owning : normal public API
owning ..> view : possible future low-level view

legend
== Logical coordinates ==
|= row y / column x |= 0 |= 1 |= 2 |= 3 |= 4 |
| 0 | (0,0) | (1,0) | (2,0) | (3,0) | (4,0) |
| 1 | (0,1) | (1,1) | (2,1) | (3,1) | (4,1) |
| 2 | (0,2) | (1,2) | (2,2) | (3,2) | (4,2) |

== Owning canvas storage: width == stride ==
|= storage index |= 0 |= 1 |= 2 |= 3 |= 4 |
| y = 0 | p00 | p10 | p20 | p30 | p40 |
| y = 1 | p01 | p11 | p21 | p31 | p41 |
| y = 2 | p02 | p12 | p22 | p32 | p42 |

index = y * width + x

== Future stride-aware storage: stride > width ==
|= storage index |= 0 |= 1 |= 2 |= 3 |= 4 |= 5 |= 6 |= 7 |
| y = 0 | p00 | p10 | p20 | p30 | p40 | pad | pad | pad |
| y = 1 | p01 | p11 | p21 | p31 | p41 | pad | pad | pad |
| y = 2 | p02 | p12 | p22 | p32 | p42 | pad | pad | pad |

index = y * stride + x

The current owning canvas does not expose physical storage references.
Normal access uses get_pixel, set_pixel, drawing, and image-processing functions.
endlegend
@enduml
